, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Waqid reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would recite in the Eid prayers, \"Qaf, by the majestic Quran,\" (50:1) and, \"The Hour approaches and the moon is cleft asunder,\" (54:1). Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 891 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0642\u0650\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062b\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19212,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/05\/21\/ikhlaas-1-3-kafirun-1-4\/","url_meta":{"origin":15682,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Surat al-Ikhlas is one-third, al-Kafirun is one-forth","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 21, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe chapter, 'Say: He is Allah the One,' (112:1) is equal to one-third of the Quran. The chapter, 'Say: O unbelievers,' (109:1) is equal to one-fourth of the Quran.\u201d Ibn Umar said, \"The Prophet would\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34004,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/02\/16\/muadh-salat-too-long\/","url_meta":{"origin":15682,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Ease: The Prophet rebukes Mu\u2019adh for long prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 16, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Abdullah reported: Mu\u2019adh ibn Jabal used to pray with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him. Then, he returned to his people and led them in prayer. Mu'adh prayed the evening prayer and recited Surat al-Baqarah, until a man left the prayer, and Mu\u2019adh was critical of\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15686,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/14\/shorter-surahs-day-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":15682,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Shorter surahs in day, longer at dawn","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 14, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Samurah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would recite in the noon prayer, \u201cBy the night as it envelopes,\u201d (92:1) and similar chapters to those in the afternoon prayer, and in the morning prayer he would recite longer than those Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 459 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4003,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/03\/two-surahs-refuge-falaq-nas\/","url_meta":{"origin":15682,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Refuge with Surat al-Falaq and al-Nas","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would seek refuge from jinn and the evil eye of man, until 'the two chapters of refuge' were revealed, al-Falaq and al-Nas. After they were revealed, he held to them and left everything else. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/15682","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=15682"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/15682\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=15682"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=15682"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=15682"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}